{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":148,"text":"I'm going to talk to you about optimism --"},{"time":3530,"text":"or more precisely, the optimism bias."},{"time":6013,"text":"It's a cognitive illusion"},{"time":7658,"text":"that we've been studying in my lab for the past few years,"},{"time":10400,"text":"and 80 percent of us have it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12135,"text":"It's our tendency to overestimate"},{"time":14869,"text":"our likelihood of experiencing good events in our lives"},{"time":17792,"text":"and underestimate our likelihood of experiencing bad events."},{"time":21900,"text":"So we underestimate our likelihood of suffering from cancer,"},{"time":24917,"text":"being in a car accident."},{"time":26423,"text":"We overestimate our longevity, our career prospects."},{"time":29609,"text":"In short, we're more optimistic than realistic,"},{"time":33054,"text":"but we are oblivious to the fact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35216,"text":"Take marriage for example."},{"time":37443,"text":"In the Western world, divorce rates are about 40 percent."},{"time":40977,"text":"That means that out of five married couples,"},{"time":44446,"text":"two will end up splitting their assets."},{"time":47167,"text":"But when you ask newlyweds about their own likelihood of divorce,"},{"time":50542,"text":"they estimate it at zero percent."},{"time":54234,"text":"And even divorce lawyers, who should really know better,"},{"time":57963,"text":"hugely underestimate their own likelihood of divorce."},{"time":61812,"text":"So it turns out that optimists are not less likely to divorce,"},{"time":64938,"text":"but they are more likely to remarry."},{"time":67468,"text":"In the words of Samuel Johnson,"},{"time":69771,"text":"\"Remarriage is the triumph of hope over experience.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":73768,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":75730,"text":"So if we're married, we're more likely to have kids."},{"time":80304,"text":"And we all think our kids will be especially talented."},{"time":83569,"text":"This, by the way, is my two-year-old nephew, Guy."},{"time":86167,"text":"And I just want to make it absolutely clear"},{"time":88542,"text":"that he's a really bad example of the optimism bias,"},{"time":91313,"text":"because he is in fact uniquely talented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94125,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":95560,"text":"And I'm not alone."},{"time":97167,"text":"Out of four British people, three said"},{"time":99642,"text":"that they were optimistic about the future of their own families."},{"time":103381,"text":"That's 75 percent."},{"time":105132,"text":"But only 30 percent said"},{"time":107190,"text":"that they thought families in general"},{"time":109750,"text":"are doing better than a few generations ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112162,"text":"And this is a really important point,"},{"time":114183,"text":"because we're optimistic about ourselves,"},{"time":116071,"text":"we're optimistic about our kids,"},{"time":117889,"text":"we're optimistic about our families,"},{"time":119677,"text":"but we're not so optimistic about the guy sitting next to us,"},{"time":122860,"text":"and we're somewhat pessimistic"},{"time":125089,"text":"about the fate of our fellow citizens and the fate of our country."},{"time":128968,"text":"But private optimism about our own personal future"},{"time":133004,"text":"remains persistent."},{"time":135015,"text":"And it doesn't mean that we think things will magically turn out okay,"},{"time":139081,"text":"but rather that we have the unique ability to make it so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143113,"text":"Now I'm a scientist, I do experiments."},{"time":145954,"text":"So to show you what I mean,"},{"time":147746,"text":"I'm going to do an experiment here with you."},{"time":150548,"text":"So I'm going to give you a list of abilities and characteristics,"},{"time":154398,"text":"and I want you to think for each of these abilities"},{"time":157292,"text":"where you stand relative to the rest of the population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161685,"text":"The first one is getting along well with others."},{"time":165471,"text":"Who here believes they're at the bottom 25 percent?"},{"time":171123,"text":"Okay, that's about 10 people out of 1,500."},{"time":175445,"text":"Who believes they're at the top 25 percent?"},{"time":179458,"text":"That's most of us here."},{"time":182168,"text":"Okay, now do the same for your driving ability."},{"time":187098,"text":"How interesting are you?"},{"time":189681,"text":"How attractive are you?"},{"time":192525,"text":"How honest are you?"},{"time":195479,"text":"And finally, how modest are you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":200479,"text":"So most of us put ourselves above average"},{"time":203167,"text":"on most of these abilities."},{"time":205196,"text":"Now this is statistically impossible."},{"time":207327,"text":"We can't all be better than everyone else."},{"time":210556,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":212198,"text":"But if we believe we're better than the other guy,"},{"time":214875,"text":"well that means that we're more likely to get that promotion, to remain married,"},{"time":218958,"text":"because we're more social, more interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221556,"text":"And it's a global phenomenon."},{"time":223719,"text":"The optimism bias has been observed"},{"time":226187,"text":"in many different countries --"},{"time":227906,"text":"in Western cultures, in non-Western cultures,"},{"time":231010,"text":"in females and males,"},{"time":232516,"text":"in kids, in the elderly."},{"time":234240,"text":"It's quite widespread."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236023,"text":"But the question is, is it good for us?"},{"time":239523,"text":"So some people say no."},{"time":241977,"text":"Some people say the secret to happiness"},{"time":244495,"text":"is low expectations."},{"time":247248,"text":"I think the logic goes something like this:"},{"time":249752,"text":"If we don't expect greatness,"},{"time":252010,"text":"if we don't expect to find love and be healthy and successful,"},{"time":255890,"text":"well we're not going to be disappointed when these things don't happen."},{"time":258988,"text":"And if we're not disappointed when good things don't happen,"},{"time":262396,"text":"and we're pleasantly surprised when they do,"},{"time":264375,"text":"we will be happy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266156,"text":"So it's a very good theory,"},{"time":267858,"text":"but it turns out to be wrong for three reasons."},{"time":270885,"text":"Number one: Whatever happens, whether you succeed or you fail,"},{"time":275500,"text":"people with high expectations always feel better."},{"time":279358,"text":"Because how we feel when we get dumped or win employee of the month"},{"time":283290,"text":"depends on how we interpret that event."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286320,"text":"The psychologists Margaret Marshall and John Brown"},{"time":290370,"text":"studied students with high and low expectations."},{"time":293364,"text":"And they found that when people with high expectations succeed,"},{"time":297548,"text":"they attribute that success to their own traits."},{"time":300458,"text":"\"I'm a genius, therefore I got an A,"},{"time":302654,"text":"therefore I'll get an A again and again in the future.\""},{"time":305329,"text":"When they failed, it wasn't because they were dumb,"},{"time":308302,"text":"but because the exam just happened to be unfair."},{"time":311475,"text":"Next time they will do better."},{"time":313758,"text":"People with low expectations do the opposite."},{"time":316835,"text":"So when they failed it was because they were dumb,"},{"time":319667,"text":"and when they succeeded"},{"time":321167,"text":"it was because the exam just happened to be really easy."},{"time":324484,"text":"Next time reality would catch up with them."},{"time":326885,"text":"So they felt worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328958,"text":"Number two: Regardless of the outcome,"},{"time":332198,"text":"the pure act of anticipation makes us happy."},{"time":336245,"text":"The behavioral economist George Lowenstein"},{"time":339421,"text":"asked students in his university"},{"time":341140,"text":"to imagine getting a passionate kiss from a celebrity, any celebrity."},{"time":345502,"text":"Then he said, \"How much are you willing to pay"},{"time":348387,"text":"to get a kiss from a celebrity"},{"time":350375,"text":"if the kiss was delivered immediately,"},{"time":352602,"text":"in three hours, in 24 hours, in three days,"},{"time":357625,"text":"in one year, in 10 years?"},{"time":360058,"text":"He found that the students were willing to pay the most"},{"time":363188,"text":"not to get a kiss immediately,"},{"time":365187,"text":"but to get a kiss in three days."},{"time":368167,"text":"They were willing to pay extra in order to wait."},{"time":372414,"text":"Now they weren't willing to wait a year or 10 years;"},{"time":375417,"text":"no one wants an aging celebrity."},{"time":376838,"text":"But three days seemed to be the optimum amount."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381627,"text":"So why is that?"},{"time":383930,"text":"Well if you get the kiss now, it's over and done with."},{"time":387354,"text":"But if you get the kiss in three days,"},{"time":389304,"text":"well that's three days of jittery anticipation, the thrill of the wait."},{"time":393458,"text":"The students wanted that time"},{"time":395327,"text":"to imagine where is it going to happen,"},{"time":397708,"text":"how is it going to happen."},{"time":399337,"text":"Anticipation made them happy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401548,"text":"This is, by the way, why people prefer Friday to Sunday."},{"time":405417,"text":"It's a really curious fact,"},{"time":407500,"text":"because Friday is a day of work and Sunday is a day of pleasure,"},{"time":410917,"text":"so you'd assume that people will prefer Sunday,"},{"time":413821,"text":"but they don't."},{"time":415542,"text":"It's not because they really, really like being in the office"},{"time":418417,"text":"and they can't stand strolling in the park"},{"time":420384,"text":"or having a lazy brunch."},{"time":422045,"text":"We know that, because when you ask people"},{"time":424181,"text":"about their ultimate favorite day of the week,"},{"time":426885,"text":"surprise, surprise, Saturday comes in at first,"},{"time":429705,"text":"then Friday, then Sunday."},{"time":432625,"text":"People prefer Friday"},{"time":434494,"text":"because Friday brings with it the anticipation of the weekend ahead,"},{"time":438458,"text":"all the plans that you have."},{"time":440375,"text":"On Sunday, the only thing you can look forward to"},{"time":443079,"text":"is the work week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445333,"text":"So optimists are people who expect more kisses in their future,"},{"time":450210,"text":"more strolls in the park."},{"time":452131,"text":"And that anticipation enhances their wellbeing."},{"time":456038,"text":"In fact, without the optimism bias,"},{"time":459002,"text":"we would all be slightly depressed."},{"time":461752,"text":"People with mild depression,"},{"time":464019,"text":"they don't have a bias when they look into the future."},{"time":466998,"text":"They're actually more realistic than healthy individuals."},{"time":471220,"text":"But individuals with severe depression,"},{"time":473321,"text":"they have a pessimistic bias."},{"time":475150,"text":"So they tend to expect the future"},{"time":477613,"text":"to be worse than it ends up being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480090,"text":"So optimism changes subjective reality."},{"time":483333,"text":"The way we expect the world to be changes the way we see it."},{"time":487083,"text":"But it also changes objective reality."},{"time":490325,"text":"It acts as a self-fulfilling prophecy."},{"time":493052,"text":"And that is the third reason"},{"time":495120,"text":"why lowering your expectations will not make you happy."},{"time":498300,"text":"Controlled experiments have shown"},{"time":500135,"text":"that optimism is not only related to success,"},{"time":503052,"text":"it leads to success."},{"time":504859,"text":"Optimism leads to success in academia and sports and politics."},{"time":509729,"text":"And maybe the most surprising benefit of optimism is health."},{"time":514204,"text":"If we expect the future to be bright,"},{"time":517529,"text":"stress and anxiety are reduced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520269,"text":"So all in all, optimism has lots of benefits."},{"time":524489,"text":"But the question that was really confusing to me was,"},{"time":527500,"text":"how do we maintain optimism in the face of reality?"},{"time":532169,"text":"As an neuroscientist, this was especially confusing,"},{"time":535187,"text":"because according to all the theories out there,"},{"time":538083,"text":"when your expectations are not met, you should alter them."},{"time":542271,"text":"But this is not what we find."},{"time":543823,"text":"We asked people to come into our lab"},{"time":547306,"text":"in order to try and figure out what was going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550116,"text":"We asked them to estimate their likelihood"},{"time":552663,"text":"of experiencing different terrible events in their lives."},{"time":555167,"text":"So, for example, what is your likelihood of suffering from cancer?"},{"time":559542,"text":"And then we told them the average likelihood"},{"time":561894,"text":"of someone like them to suffer these misfortunes."},{"time":564875,"text":"So cancer, for example, is about 30 percent."},{"time":568440,"text":"And then we asked them again,"},{"time":571375,"text":"\"How likely are you to suffer from cancer?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":574250,"text":"What we wanted to know was"},{"time":576498,"text":"whether people will take the information that we gave them"},{"time":579167,"text":"to change their beliefs."},{"time":581298,"text":"And indeed they did --"},{"time":583667,"text":"but mostly when the information we gave them"},{"time":586248,"text":"was better than what they expected."},{"time":589079,"text":"So for example,"},{"time":590440,"text":"if someone said, \"My likelihood of suffering from cancer"},{"time":593350,"text":"is about 50 percent,\""},{"time":595731,"text":"and we said, \"Hey, good news."},{"time":598252,"text":"The average likelihood is only 30 percent,\""},{"time":600833,"text":"the next time around they would say,"},{"time":602879,"text":"\"Well maybe my likelihood is about 35 percent.\""},{"time":605594,"text":"So they learned quickly and efficiently."},{"time":608230,"text":"But if someone started off saying,"},{"time":610780,"text":"\"My average likelihood of suffering from cancer is about 10 percent,\""},{"time":614183,"text":"and we said, \"Hey, bad news."},{"time":616875,"text":"The average likelihood is about 30 percent,\""},{"time":619948,"text":"the next time around they would say,"},{"time":622006,"text":"\"Yep. Still think it's about 11 percent.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":625125,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":626815,"text":"So it's not that they didn't learn at all -- they did --"},{"time":630134,"text":"but much, much less than when we gave them"},{"time":632470,"text":"positive information about the future."},{"time":634943,"text":"And it's not that they didn't remember the numbers that we gave them;"},{"time":637977,"text":"everyone remembers that the average likelihood of cancer"},{"time":641050,"text":"is about 30 percent"},{"time":642550,"text":"and the average likelihood of divorce is about 40 percent."},{"time":645329,"text":"But they didn't think that those numbers were related to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649960,"text":"What this means is that warning signs such as these"},{"time":654108,"text":"may only have limited impact."},{"time":657000,"text":"Yes, smoking kills, but mostly it kills the other guy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661159,"text":"What I wanted to know was"},{"time":663042,"text":"what was going on inside the human brain"},{"time":665902,"text":"that prevented us from taking these warning signs personally."},{"time":669996,"text":"But at the same time,"},{"time":671483,"text":"when we hear that the housing market is hopeful,"},{"time":673461,"text":"we think, \"Oh, my house is definitely going to double in price.\""},{"time":677577,"text":"To try and figure that out,"},{"time":679662,"text":"I asked the participants in the experiment"},{"time":682135,"text":"to lie in a brain imaging scanner."},{"time":684296,"text":"It looks like this."},{"time":685823,"text":"And using a method called functional MRI,"},{"time":688854,"text":"we were able to identify regions in the brain"},{"time":692460,"text":"that were responding to positive information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695277,"text":"One of these regions is called the left inferior frontal gyrus."},{"time":698856,"text":"So if someone said, \"My likelihood of suffering from cancer is 50 percent,\""},{"time":702644,"text":"and we said, \"Hey, good news."},{"time":704500,"text":"Average likelihood is 30 percent,\""},{"time":706790,"text":"the left inferior frontal gyrus would respond fiercely."},{"time":710362,"text":"And it didn't matter if you're an extreme optimist, a mild optimist"},{"time":715094,"text":"or slightly pessimistic,"},{"time":716915,"text":"everyone's left inferior frontal gyrus"},{"time":719500,"text":"was functioning perfectly well,"},{"time":721344,"text":"whether you're Barack Obama or Woody Allen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724250,"text":"On the other side of the brain,"},{"time":725894,"text":"the right inferior frontal gyrus was responding to bad news."},{"time":730680,"text":"And here's the thing: it wasn't doing a very good job."},{"time":734406,"text":"The more optimistic you were,"},{"time":736421,"text":"the less likely this region was"},{"time":738758,"text":"to respond to unexpected negative information."},{"time":741740,"text":"And if your brain is failing"},{"time":744798,"text":"at integrating bad news about the future,"},{"time":748023,"text":"you will constantly leave your rose-tinted spectacles on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752646,"text":"So we wanted to know, could we change this?"},{"time":757615,"text":"Could we alter people's optimism bias"},{"time":761058,"text":"by interfering with the brain activity in these regions?"},{"time":764990,"text":"And there's a way for us to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767585,"text":"This is my collaborator Ryota Kanai."},{"time":770212,"text":"And what he's doing is he's passing a small magnetic pulse"},{"time":774167,"text":"through the skull of the participant in our study"},{"time":776286,"text":"into their inferior frontal gyrus."},{"time":778531,"text":"And by doing that,"},{"time":780458,"text":"he's interfering with the activity of this brain region"},{"time":783362,"text":"for about half an hour."},{"time":784577,"text":"After that everything goes back to normal, I assure you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787498,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":789491,"text":"So let's see what happens."},{"time":792645,"text":"First of all, I'm going to show you"},{"time":794742,"text":"the average amount of bias that we see."},{"time":797446,"text":"So if I was to test all of you now,"},{"time":800269,"text":"this is the amount that you would learn"},{"time":802063,"text":"more from good news relative to bad news."},{"time":805183,"text":"Now we interfere with the region"},{"time":807667,"text":"that we found to integrate negative information in this task,"},{"time":812134,"text":"and the optimism bias grew even larger."},{"time":815698,"text":"We made people more biased in the way that they process information."},{"time":821168,"text":"Then we interfered with the brain region"},{"time":824065,"text":"that we found to integrate good news in this task,"},{"time":827583,"text":"and the optimism bias disappeared."},{"time":832054,"text":"We were quite amazed by these results"},{"time":834062,"text":"because we were able to eliminate"},{"time":836254,"text":"a deep-rooted bias in humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839450,"text":"And at this point we stopped and we asked ourselves,"},{"time":844223,"text":"would we want to shatter the optimism illusion into tiny little bits?"},{"time":849325,"text":"If we could do that, would we want to take people's optimism bias away?"},{"time":854369,"text":"Well I've already told you about all of the benefits of the optimism bias,"},{"time":858969,"text":"which probably makes you want to hold onto it for dear life."},{"time":863290,"text":"But there are, of course, pitfalls,"},{"time":865375,"text":"and it would be really foolish of us to ignore them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":868495,"text":"Take for example this email I recieved"},{"time":872041,"text":"from a firefighter here in California."},{"time":874735,"text":"He says, \"Fatality investigations for firefighters"},{"time":878039,"text":"often include 'We didn't think the fire was going to do that,'"},{"time":882181,"text":"even when all of the available information"},{"time":884483,"text":"was there to make safe decisions.\""},{"time":886738,"text":"This captain is going to use our findings on the optimism bias"},{"time":890612,"text":"to try to explain to the firefighters"},{"time":892804,"text":"why they think the way they do,"},{"time":895013,"text":"to make them acutely aware of this very optimistic bias in humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902139,"text":"So unrealistic optimism can lead to risky behavior,"},{"time":907258,"text":"to financial collapse, to faulty planning."},{"time":910896,"text":"The British government, for example,"},{"time":913034,"text":"has acknowledged that the optimism bias"},{"time":915708,"text":"can make individuals more likely"},{"time":918995,"text":"to underestimate the costs and durations of projects."},{"time":923021,"text":"So they have adjusted the 2012 Olympic budget"},{"time":927275,"text":"for the optimism bias."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929386,"text":"My friend who's getting married in a few weeks"},{"time":931573,"text":"has done the same for his wedding budget."},{"time":934007,"text":"And by the way, when I asked him about his own likelihood of divorce,"},{"time":937069,"text":"he said he was quite sure it was zero percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940629,"text":"So what we would really like to do,"},{"time":943046,"text":"is we would like to protect ourselves from the dangers of optimism,"},{"time":947207,"text":"but at the same time remain hopeful,"},{"time":950435,"text":"benefiting from the many fruits of optimism."},{"time":953279,"text":"And I believe there's a way for us to do that."},{"time":956083,"text":"The key here really is knowledge."},{"time":958143,"text":"We're not born with an innate understanding of our biases."},{"time":961454,"text":"These have to be identified by scientific investigation."},{"time":965295,"text":"But the good news is that becoming aware of the optimism bias"},{"time":969479,"text":"does not shatter the illusion."},{"time":971254,"text":"It's like visual illusions,"},{"time":972802,"text":"in which understanding them does not make them go away."},{"time":976292,"text":"And this is good because it means"},{"time":978529,"text":"we should be able to strike a balance,"},{"time":981002,"text":"to come up with plans and rules"},{"time":983429,"text":"to protect ourselves from unrealistic optimism,"},{"time":986212,"text":"but at the same time remain hopeful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":989364,"text":"I think this cartoon portrays it nicely."},{"time":992788,"text":"Because if you're one of these pessimistic penguins up there"},{"time":996314,"text":"who just does not believe they can fly,"},{"time":998433,"text":"you certainly never will."},{"time":1000792,"text":"Because to make any kind of progress,"},{"time":1002623,"text":"we need to be able to imagine a different reality,"},{"time":1004973,"text":"and then we need to believe that that reality is possible."},{"time":1008714,"text":"But if you are an extreme optimistic penguin"},{"time":1012238,"text":"who just jumps down blindly hoping for the best,"},{"time":1015000,"text":"you might find yourself in a bit of a mess when you hit the ground."},{"time":1019781,"text":"But if you're an optimistic penguin"},{"time":1021670,"text":"who believes they can fly,"},{"time":1023466,"text":"but then adjusts a parachute to your back"},{"time":1026129,"text":"just in case things don't work out exactly as you had planned,"},{"time":1029146,"text":"you will soar like an eagle,"},{"time":1031009,"text":"even if you're just a penguin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1034058,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1035820,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}